@Aldyn From what I understand, it's because he still feels worry about keeping the relationship alive for as long as they live. Just how long can they keep this secret just so they can stay together? Just how much time do they have left to indulge in this genuine relationship knowing that there are very strict rules governing the society we live in that forbids this kind of relationship. Like the brother said in one of the previous books, they won't ever get the priveledge of being recognized as a normal couple by society and will have to forego many things just to defy the rules and stay with each other. 

I also think that the brother is scared of how fast Yui is growing. Children especially in their teens are in that stage of their life where they begin to choose or at least have an idea of what kinds of things and people they'll want to stay with or let go in the future. He's scared that if he leaves Yui's side, she'd have grown out of their relationship and be with someone else.

Just created an account to express how this series is the magnum opus of any doujinshi ever created that I have seen in my lifetime (obviously biased). Specifically this story really captures for me not the feeling of guilty pleasure of incest or lolicon (although I do like them) rather the underlying longing for a platonic and erotic relationship that I think everyone desires to have but cannot seem to find. Moreover, by using this distant-in-age pair of siblings it not only shows familial affection that people do not exhibit nowadays (talking about the platonic parts), but also illustrates how beautiful a loyal and loving connection to another is by conveying how they can overcome their circumstances and stay devoted to each other despite their taboo relationship.
